name: training
notes: Excludes any multi-card PINs, therefore unit of observation is PIN

name: assessment
notes: Includes all cards that need valuation

name: complex_id
notes: Only run as-needed i.e. as little as possible

name: land_site_rate
notes: Site-specific flat land values provided by Valuations for 210 and 295s only

name: land_nbhd_rate
notes: Neighborhood-level land rates (per sqft) provided by Valuations

name: metadata
notes: Information about each run

name: parameter_default
notes: Default set of model parameters pulled from the included .Renviron file

name: parameter_search
notes: Each row is the result from one fold assessment from one iteration

name: parameter_raw
notes: Raw output from CV/tuning. Not useful in Athena but needed to make models reproducible

name: parameter_final
notes: Best hyperparameters for each run, as chosen by tune::select_best()

name: parameter_range
notes: CV search range per parameter per run

name: test
notes: Input test data with model prediction attached. Saved temporarily for use in evaluate stage

name: workflow_fit
notes: Trained model object saved for future use

name: workflow_recipe
notes: Trained recipe object. Can be used to prepare new data in the same way as the original model training

name: assessment
notes: Assessment results AGGREGATED to the PIN level. Model predictions are added together in the case of multi-card PINs. This is the data used for performance evaluation by the evaluate stage

name: assessment_card
notes: Assessment results at the card level. Multi-card PINs will have more than one row. NOTE: Each run adds new partitions to S3 which must be added via a Glue crawler

name: assessment_pin
notes: Assessment results at the PIN level. Includes PIN-level stats like YoY % changes, sales, etc. NOTE: Each run adds new partitions to S3 which must be added via a Glue crawler

name: performance_test
primary_key: year, run_id, stage, geography_type, geography_id, by_class, class
notes: Peformance metrics (optionally) broken out by class for different levels of geography

name: performance_assessment
primary_key: year, run_id, stage, geography_type, geography_id, by_class, class
notes: Peformance metrics (optionally) broken out by class for different levels of geography

name: performance_quantile_test
primary_key: year, run_id, stage, geography_type, geography_id, by_class, class, quantile
notes: Performance metrics by quantile within class and geography

name: performance_quantile_assessment
primary_key: year, run_id, stage, geography_type, geography_id, by_class, class, quantile
notes: Performance metrics by quantile within class and geography

name: shap
notes: SHAP values for each feature of each card in the assessment data. NOTE: Each run adds new partitions to S3 which must be added via a Glue crawler

name: timing
notes: Intermediate collection of timings for each stage. Converted into a one-row data frame in the finalize stage

name: timing
notes: Timings for whole run. Each row represents one run, while columns represent the stages
